Name: Dijkstra
Key_Insight: Curvature=0 → 1 optimum → O(V²). Non-negative weights = bounded curvature. Greedy choice = local optimum = global. The degenerate P=NP case everyone already accepted

Name: Fixed Depth Collapse
Key_Insight: d-bounded ∃∀∃∀... = O(d × poly(n)) = P for constant d

Name: State Space Bound
Key_Insight: poly(n) state bits → PSPACE; 2^poly(n) → EXPTIME. Bound s → collapse

Name: White Noise Collapse
Key_Insight: Unbounded = א^א = incomputable; Bounded = structured = P. Universe finite → computable

Name: Syllable Saturation
Key_Insight: V/C patterns saturate to syllable boundaries in O(n) without explicit HMM

Name: Curvature Geodesics
Key_Insight: Bounded κ → polynomial geodesics → polynomial SAT. Ollivier-Ricci on constraint graphs

Name: SHA-256 Curvature
Key_Insight: Full 64-round SHA-256 |κ| < 1. 37K vars 125K clauses bounded. Poly preimage search

Name: Two Randomness
Key_Insight: Bit-level K(x)≈|x| (crypto) vs Physics-level K(x)<<|x| (sensors). 35% compression gap. BQP=P via physical gates

Name: Sparse Optimization
Key_Insight: O(n^c) optima → O(log n) samples → (1+ε)-approx. κ guides dense vs sparse. Triangle 18

Name: Sparse-Bounded-DP
Key_Insight: Bounded locality c=O(1) enables O(n) DP refinement. Sparse O(log n) + Bounded DP O(n) = O(n). Unifies proximal sort and DTW refinement

Name: Bounded Displacement Sort
Key_Insight: Bounded displacement d=O(1) enables O(n) sorting via propagation. Ω(n log n) applies to S_complete (adversarial) not S_observable (bounded)
